      <title>Markdown -- Lightweight Markup Language</title>
      <link>https://yana-nka.github.io/my-academic-site/en/post/markdown-lightweight/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://yana-nka.github.io/my-academic-site/en/post/markdown-lightweight/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-is-markdown&#34;&gt;What is Markdown?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Markdown is a lightweight markup language created by John Gruber in 2004. It allows you to format plain text using simple, intuitive syntax and convert it to HTML.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;basic-syntax&#34;&gt;Basic Syntax&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;headers&#34;&gt;Headers&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;header-1&#34;&gt;Header 1&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;header-2&#34;&gt;Header 2&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;header-3&#34;&gt;Header 3&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;lists&#34;&gt;Lists&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Item 1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Item 2
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sub-item&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;links-and-images&#34;&gt;Links and Images&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;url&#34;&gt;Link text&lt;/a&gt;
















&lt;figure  &gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;&lt;img src=&#34;image.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Alt text&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;code&#34;&gt;Code&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inline code or code blocks with triple backticks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;applications&#34;&gt;Applications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Documentation&lt;/strong&gt; for software projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blogs&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; static site generators (like Hugo)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge management&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; Notion, Obsidian&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chat platforms&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; Discord, Telegram, Slack&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Developer platforms&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; GitHub README files&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;conclusion&#34;&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Markdown is a simple, convenient format that has become the standard for documentation and text formatting on the web.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
